design:
Based on beads ready.go, adapted for Phase 1 (in-memory + petgraph):

**Algorithm** (Phase 1 - petgraph):
1. Find directly blocked issues (via 'blocks' deps to open/in_progress issues)
2. Recursively propagate blockage through parent-child deps (depth limit 50)
3. Exclude all blocked issues from results

**Phase 1 Implementation**:
```rust
impl InMemoryStorage {
    fn find_ready(&self, filter: Option<&IssueFilter>) -> Result<Vec<Issue>> {
        use petgraph::Direction;

        // Find all blocked issues
        let mut blocked = HashSet::new();

        // Direct blocks: issues with blocking dependencies
        for (id, issue) in &self.issues {
            if issue.status == Status::Closed {
                continue;
            }

            for dep in &issue.dependencies {
                if dep.dep_type == DependencyType::Blocks {
                    let blocker = self.issues.get(&dep.depends_on_id)?;
                    if blocker.status == Status::Open || blocker.status == Status::InProgress {
                        blocked.insert(id.clone());
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // Transitive blocking via parent-child (BFS with depth limit)
        let mut to_process: VecDeque<(IssueId, usize)> = blocked.iter()
            .map(|id| (id.clone(), 0))
            .collect();

        while let Some((id, depth)) = to_process.pop_front() {
            if depth >= 50 { continue; }

            // Find children (issues that depend on this one via parent-child)
            let node = self.node_map.get(&id)?;
            for edge in self.graph.edges_directed(*node, Direction::Incoming) {
                if edge.weight() == &DependencyType::ParentChild {
                    let child_node = edge.source();
                    let child_id = &self.graph[child_node];
                    if blocked.insert(child_id.clone()) {
                        to_process.push_back((child_id.clone(), depth + 1));
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // Filter out blocked issues
        let mut ready: Vec<Issue> = self.issues.values()
            .filter(|issue| {
                issue.status != Status::Closed 
                && !blocked.contains(&issue.id)
            })
            .cloned()
            .collect();

        // Apply additional filter if provided
        if let Some(filter) = filter {
            ready = self.apply_filter(ready, filter)?;
        }

        // Sort by policy (hybrid default)
        self.sort_by_policy(&mut ready, SortPolicy::Hybrid);

        Ok(ready)
    }
}
```

**Sort Policies**:
- `hybrid` (default): Recent (48h) by priority, older by age
- `priority`: P0→P1→P2→P3→P4 strict
- `oldest`: Creation date ascending

**Phase 3 (PostgreSQL)**: Will use recursive CTEs for blocking propagation (see design notes)

